    "department": "Product Management \u0026 Design",
    "description": "Join Ema Unlimited, a pioneering company at the forefront of Generative AI technology. We are seeking a talented Product Designer to contribute to the development of Ema, our Universal AI Employee. In this role, you will design user experiences that simplify complex workflows and enhance productivity for enterprises globally.\n\n\nABOUT EMA\n\nEma is building the next generation AI technology to empower every employee in the enterprise to be their most creative and productive. Our proprietary tech allows enterprises to delegate most repetitive tasks to Ema, the AI employee. We are founded by ex-Google, Coinbase, Okta executives and serial entrepreneurs. We’ve raised capital from notable investors such as Accel Partners, Naspers, Section32 and a host of prominent Silicon Valley Angels including Sheryl Sandberg (Facebook/Google), Divesh Makan (Iconiq Capital), Jerry Yang (Yahoo), Dustin Moskovitz (Facebook/Asana), David Baszucki (Roblox CEO) and Gokul Rajaram (Doordash, Square, Google).\n\nOur team is a powerhouse of talent, comprising engineers from leading tech companies like Google, Microsoft Research, Facebook, Square/Block, and Coinbase. All our team members hail from top-tier educational institutions such as Stanford, MIT, UC Berkeley, CMU and Indian Institute of Technology.  We’re well funded by the top investors and angels in the world. Ema is based in Silicon Valley and Bangalore, India. This will be a hybrid role where we expect employees to work from the office three days a week.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nWe are seeking a talented Product Designer to contribute to the development of Ema, our Universal AI Employee. In this role, you will design user experiences that simplify complex workflows and enhance productivity for enterprises globally.\n\nRoles and Responsibilities:\n\n - User-Centered Design: Create intuitive and visually appealing user interfaces by considering market analysis, data insights, customer feedback, and technical constraints.\n\n - Collaboration: Work closely with cross-functional teams including user research, engineering, and product management to bring design concepts to life.\n\n - Prototyping: Quickly and thoroughly develop user flows, wireframes, design mockups, and prototypes to conceptualize new product initiatives.\n\n - Simplification: Relentlessly simplify and distill complex processes into elegant and user-friendly interfaces.\n\n - Consistency: Establish and maintain detailed user-interface patterns and design system specifications, ensuring consistent application across all products\n\n - Communication: Effectively communicate complex design concepts across various audiences and organizational levels.\n\n - Continuous Improvement: Incorporate feedback from users and team members to continuously improve the design and functionality of our products.\n\nQualifications:\n\n - Experience: 5+ years of experience in UX/UI design, with a portfolio showcasing your ability to create intuitive and user-centered designs.\n\n - Technical Skills: Proficiency in design tools such as Figma, Sketch or similar. Strong understanding of current web technologies and best practices.\n\n - Analytical Skills: Ability to use data to inform design decisions and demonstrate a critical awareness of the implications on user-centered design.\n\n - Detail-Oriented: Strong attention to detail with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.\n\n - Team Player: Comfortable working on technical teams and collaborating across different departments.\n\n - Education: Bachelor’s degree in Design, Human-Computer Interaction (HCI), or a related field.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\n - Examples of Shipped Work: Demonstrated experience with shipped work across multiple platforms.\n\n - Mentorship: Experience mentoring junior designers.\n\n - Innovation: Passion for learning and driving innovation in UX design.\n\n\nWHY EMA UNLIMITED?\n\n - Innovative Technology: Be a part of a groundbreaking company transforming enterprise workflows with Generative AI.\n\n - Talented Team: Work alongside a powerhouse team of engineers and designers from leading tech companies and top-tier educational institutions.\n\n - Growth Opportunities: Ema Unlimited is backed by prominent investors, providing ample opportunities for professional growth and development.\n\n - Hybrid Work Environment: Enjoy the flexibility of a hybrid work setup, with the opportunity to collaborate in our Mountain View offices.\n\nJoin us at Ema Unlimited and help shape the future of enterprise productivity with cutting-edge AI technology.\n\nEma Unlimited is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, or genetics.",
